cs.MS, cs.NA, cs.DC, cs.CE, cs.OH 

Reasoning: 
- cs.MS (Mathematical Software) is the most likely category as the paper discusses the use of the Automatic Differentiation tool TAPENADE to build the tangent and adjoint codes of the ocean general circulation model OPA. 
- cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) is also likely as the paper discusses the implementation of state-of-the-art methods to improve the performance of the adjoint code. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is a possibility as the paper mentions the implementation of the Griewank and Walther's binomial checkpointing algorithm to optimize time and memory consumption. 
- cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) is a possibility as the paper discusses the development of a model for ocean general circulation. 
- cs.OH (Other Computer Science) is a possibility as the paper does not fit neatly into any specific sub-category and covers a range of topics including software development, numerical analysis, and computational modeling.
